[src:cache-poisoning-defense/http-headers-cheat-sheet] As described in the Apache documentation, `Header set` (default `onsuccess`) and `Header always set` operate on separate internal header tables.
[src:cache-poisoning-defense/http-headers-cheat-sheet] In some cases, both header tables may be used, which can result in duplicate headers if the same header is configured in both contexts.
[src:cache-poisoning-defense/http-headers-cheat-sheet] If a header needs to be removed entirely, it should be unset in both contexts (`onsuccess` and `always`).
